## ⚙️ Setup

### 1. Install Dependencies

```bash
<%= packageManager %> install
```

### 2. Configure Environment Variables

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Open `.env` and update your database credentials and any other required values.

### 3. Run Database Migrations

<% if (orm === 'prisma') { %>
```bash
npx prisma migrate dev
```
<% } else if (orm === 'sequelize') { %>
```bash
npx sequelize-cli db:migrate
```
<% } else if (orm === 'mongoose' || orm === 'none') { %>
> No migrations needed for this setup.
<% } %>

### 4. Start the Development Server

```bash
<%= packageManager %> run dev
```

The server will start at **http://localhost:3000** (or the port defined in your `.env`).

---

## 📜 Available Scripts

| Script | Description |
|---|---|
| `<%= packageManager %> run dev` | Start with hot-reload (nodemon) |
| `<%= packageManager %> run start` | Start in production mode |
| `<%= packageManager %> run lint` | Run ESLint |
| `<%= packageManager %> run test` | Run test suite |

---

## 🔐 Environment Variables

| Variable | Description | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `PORT` | Server port | `3000` |
| `NODE_ENV` | Environment | `development` |
| `DATABASE_URL` | Database connection string | `<%= database %>://user:pass@localhost/db` |

